A tragic incident unfolded as a bridge over the Mississippi River collapsed during rush hour, claiming at least six lives.
The catastrophic scene showed vehicles submerged in the river amidst smoke and flames.
The bridge was under construction and reports suggest engineering issues may have led to the collapse.
Despite fears of terrorism, officials confirmed no such link.
Rescue efforts were hindered by the dangerous conditions, with hopes of finding survivors dwindling.
Investigations are underway to piece together the cause of this devastating event, shedding light on structural deficiencies that were previously overlooked.
